{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πῦρ</b> <br /> (once <b>πύυρ</b> [?~X ¯ ?~X] by 'distraction', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Simonides Lyricus 59 codices Hdn.Gr. (“Rh.Mus.” 35.101, 38.378)), τό, _genitive_ πῠρός\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; not used in <i>plural</i>, see at {πυρά},{τά}:—<b>fire</b>, π. καίειν or δαίειν to kindle <b>fire</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 8.521, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 7.7, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; π. ἀνακαίειν, ἅπτειν, ἐξάπτειν, αἴθειν, ἐναύειν, (see entry).; π. ποιεῖν, ποιήσασθαι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Anaxippus Comicus 1.12, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 5.2.27; οἴσετε π. 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 15.718; π. προσέφερον 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 5.2.14 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; π. ἐμβαλεῖν νηυσί, κλισίῃσι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 15.597, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.501 (tmesis)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; π. φυσητέον, ῥιπίζειν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 293, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Flamininus” 21; as exclamation, πῦρ βοᾷ 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Σαμία” 208. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__b</b></Level4> π. τεχνικόν, see at {τεχνικός}. <br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>funeral-fire</b> (compare πυρά), ὄφρα πυρός με.. λελάχωσι θανόντα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 7.79, 22.342, compare 15.350, 23.76 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ζῶντα διδόναι τινὰ πυρί <b>burn</b> one alive, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.86. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>sacrificial fire</b>, ἐν πυρὶ βάλλε θυηλάς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 9.220, compare 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 3.341, 446; κατὰ τοῦ π. σπένδειν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Critias” 120a; διὰ τοῦ π. ὀμνύναι 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 54.40. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <b>hearthfire</b>, πυρὸς ἐσχάραι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 10.418, compare 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 5.59; ἕως ἂν αἴθῃ πῦρ ἐφ᾽ ἑστίας ἐμῆς 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1435; πυρὶ δέχεσθαί τινα 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 47 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ π. τὸ ἀθάνατον <b>the fire</b> of Vesta, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Numa” 9, etc.; deified, Πῦρ ἀθάνατον “SIG” 826 ii 14 (Delph., 2nd c.BC). \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> <b>lightning</b>, κεραυνὸς ἀενάου πυρός [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 1.6; πῦρ πνέοντος κεραυνοῦ [prev. author] “fragment” 146; πυρὸς ἀμφήκης βόστρυχος 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 1044 (_anapaest meter_); πυρὶ καὶ στεροπαῖς 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 470 (_anapaest meter_); παλτῷ ῥιπτεῖ πυρί [prev. author] “Ant.” 131 (_anapaest meter_); θείῳ πυρὶ παμφαής [prev. author] “Ph.” 728 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__5.b</b></Level4> <b>fire, light</b>, or <b>heat</b> of the sun, θερινὸν π., opposed to χειμών, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 3.50, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 865b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the stars, π. πνείοντα ἄστρα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 1146 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>summer solstice</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th c.BC: Alcman Lyricus 79, 4th c.AD: Paulus Alexandrinus Astrologus “A.” 3. \">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__6</b></Level3> <b>flame</b> of torches, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 964 (Lyric poetry), etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; π. εὐάγγελον, ἄγγαρον, πομπόν, of the beacon fire, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 21, 282, 299. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__7</b></Level3> <b>fever heat, violent fever</b>, πῦρ ἔλαβέν [τινα] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “ἐπιδημίαι” 1.26.ή, +others\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὁ δ᾽ ἔχων θέρμαν καὶ π. ἧκεν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Fragmenta” 690; τεταρταίῳ πυρί 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Aetia” 3.1.17; π. ἄγριον 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “ἐπιδημίαι” 7.20 (of erysipelas _accusative_ to 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 19.134). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> phrases, ἐν πυρὶ γενέσθαι to be consumed, come to nothing, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.340 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; φεύγων καπνὸν εἰς πῦρ δεσποτείας ἐμπεπτωκώς 'out of the frying pan into the <b>fire</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 569b, cf. Prov. cited in 6th c.AD: Simplicius Philosophus “in Epictetum commentaria” p.72 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator; ἦν ἄρα πυρός γ᾽ ἕτερα θερμότερα 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 382 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πῦρ ἐπὶ πῦρ ἐγχεῖν, ἄγειν, φέρειν, ἐπεισφέρειν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 18, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Fragmenta” 453, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Problemata” 880a21, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.61a\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; εἰς π. ξαίνειν 'plough the sands', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 780c; βασανίζειν χρυσὸν ἐν πυρί [prev. author] “R.” 413e, compare 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 21.20.7 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: as a type of things <b>irresistible</b> or <b>terrible</b>, ἀντίος εἶμι, καὶ εἰ πυρὶ χεῖρας ἔοικε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 20.371; μάρναντο δέμας πυρὸς αἰθομένοιο 11.596, +others; Ἕκτωρ πυρὸς αἰνὸν ἔχει μένος 17.565, compare 6.182; so τὸ πεπρωμένον οὐ π. σχήσει 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “Fragmenta.” 232; κρεῖσσον ἀμαιμακέτου πυρός 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 177; οὐδὲν θηρίον γυναικὸς ἀμαχώτερον, οὐδὲ π. 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 1015; ἀναρχία κρείσσων πυρός 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 608; ἐχίδνης καὶ πυρὸς περαιτέρω [prev. author] “Andr.” 271 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; so διὰ πυρὸς ἰέναι (as we say) to go through <b>fire and water</b>, dash through any danger, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Symposium” 4.16, compare “Oec.” 21.7, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 133 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; but διὰ πυρὸς ἦλθε ἑτέρῳ λέχεϊ she <b>raged furiously</b> against the other partner of the bed, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Andromache” 487 (Lyric poetry); διὰ πυρὸς ἔμολον ματρί [prev. author] “El.” 1183 (Lyric poetry); σωθήσεται οὕτω δὲ ὡς διὰ πυρός NT.1Cor.3.15; εἰς π. ἅλλεσθαι 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 1.3.9; κἂν εἰς π. ἐμβαῖεν 4th c.AD: Libanius Sophista “Epistulae” 314.3; π. διέρπειν 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 265 \">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]; of persons, ὦ π. σύ.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ph.” 927 \">Refs</a>]; of Hannibal, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Flamininus” 21 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]: <i>metaphorically</i> of anxious hope, θάλπει τῷδ᾽ ἀνηκέστῳ πυρί [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 888 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of love, ἀρσενικῷ θέρεται π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Epigrammata” 27.5, compare 45.2 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]. (Cf. Armenian <i>hur</i>, O[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>fyr</b> 'fire', etc.)","strongNumber":"G4442","accentedUnicode":"πῦρ","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0329","matchingForm":"ἀναζωπυρέω","stepTransliteration":"anazōpureō","gloss":"to rekindle","_zh_tw_Gloss":"重燃","_es_Gloss":"reavivar","_zh_Gloss":"重燃"},{"strongNumber":"G2200","matchingForm":"ζεστός","stepTransliteration":"zestos","gloss":"hot","_zh_tw_Gloss":"熱","_es_Gloss":"caliente","_zh_Gloss":"热"},{"strongNumber":"G2204","matchingForm":"ζέω","stepTransliteration":"zeō","gloss":"be fervent","_zh_tw_Gloss":"要火熱, 火熱","_es_Gloss":"ser ferviente","_zh_Gloss":"要火热, 火热"},{"strongNumber":"G2205","matchingForm":"ζῆλος","stepTransliteration":"zēlos","gloss":"zeal","_zh_tw_Gloss":"熱心, 嫉妒","_es_Gloss":"fervor","_zh_Gloss":"热心, 嫉妒"},{"strongNumber":"G2206","matchingForm":"ζηλόω","stepTransliteration":"zēloō","gloss":"be eager","_zh_tw_Gloss":"要切慕","_es_Gloss":"estar ansioso","_zh_Gloss":"要切慕"},{"strongNumber":"G2207","matchingForm":"ζηλωτής","stepTransliteration":"zēlōtēs","gloss":"zealot","_zh_tw_Gloss":"熱心","_es_Gloss":"seguidor dedicado","_zh_Gloss":"热心"},{"strongNumber":"G2208","matchingForm":"ζηλωτής","stepTransliteration":"zēlōtēs","gloss":"Zealot","_searchResultRange":"Luke.6.15-Acts.1.13@Matt.10.4-Acts.1.13","_zh_tw_Gloss":"奮銳黨","_es_Gloss":"zelote/celota","_zh_Gloss":"奋锐党"},{"strongNumber":"G3863","matchingForm":"παραζηλόω","stepTransliteration":"parazēloō","gloss":"to make envious","_zh_tw_Gloss":"引起嫉妒","_es_Gloss":"hacer envidioso","_zh_Gloss":"引起嫉妒"},{"strongNumber":"G4443","matchingForm":"πυρά","stepTransliteration":"pura","gloss":"fire","_zh_tw_Gloss":"火","_es_Gloss":"fuego","_zh_Gloss":"火"},{"strongNumber":"G4445","matchingForm":"πυρέσσω","stepTransliteration":"puressō","gloss":"be feverish","_zh_tw_Gloss":"害熱病","_es_Gloss":"tener fiebre","_zh_Gloss":"害热病"},{"strongNumber":"G4